message.entry: IndexNames must be a cell vector.
IndexNames must have at least as many elements as number of dimensions in the array.
Each element of IndexNames must be a cell array of character vectors, a string vector or empty.
The number of strings or character vectors in each element of IndexNames must match the length of the corresponding dimension.
The strings or character vectors in each element of IndexNames must be non-empty.
Elements of InputNames must be empty or a single string or character vector in trailing dimensions.
Illegal use of '':'' as an index name.
Illegal use of '':'' as an index name in dimension {0}.
Dimensions specifications must be a positive integer, string array, or a cell array of character vectors.
Scalar strings must be contained in a cell array.

OptimizationVariables appearing in the same problem, constraint, or expression must have distinct "Name" properties.\n Make a new variable with a different "Name" property, or retrieve the original variable using the Variables property.
